@@TJvCustomListBox.CreateDragImage
Summary
  Creates a drag image of the specified string.
Description
  CreateDragImage is called whenever the user begins to drag an item in the list box by left-clicking
  \on that item and holding the mouse button down, and no OnStartDrag handler is specified.

  It creates a drag image of the string specified by the S parameter. The image will appear next to the
  mouse cursor during the drag operation.

  You can call CreateDragImage in an OnStartDrag event handler to let the list box handle the start
  drag event in a default way.
Parameters
  S - Specifies the item being dragged.
See Also
  <LINK TJvCustomListBox.DefaultDragDrop, DefaultDragDrop>,
  <LINK TJvCustomListBox.DefaultDragOver, DefaultDragOver>,
  <LINK TJvCustomListBox.DefaultStartDrag, DefaultStartDrag>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.DefaultDragDrop
Summary
  Handles a drop event.
Description
  DefaultDragDrop is called whenever the user drops an object being dragged, and no OnDragDrop handler
  is specified.

  It moves the item being dragged to its drop position.

  You can call DefaultDragDrop in an OnDragDrop event handler to let the list box handle the drop event
  in a default way.
Parameters
  Source - The object being dropped.
  X      - Horizon screen coordinate of the mouse in pixels.
  Y      - Vertical screen coordinate of the mouse in pixels.
See Also
  <LINK TJvCustomListBox.CreateDragImage, CreateDragImage>,
  <LINK TJvCustomListBox.DefaultStartDrag, DefaultDragOver>,
  <LINK TJvCustomListBox.DefaultStartDrag, DefaultStartDrag>,
  TControl.OnDragDrop
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.DefaultDragOver
Summary
  Handles a drag over event.
Description
  DefaultDragOver is called whenever the user drags an object over the list box, and no OnDragOver
  handler is specified.

  You can call DefaultDragOver in an OnDragOver event handler to let the list box handle the drag over
  event in a default way.
Parameters
  Source - The object being dragged.
  X      - Horizon screen coordinate of the mouse in pixels.
  Y      - Vertical screen coordinate of the mouse in pixels.
  State  - Specifies how the dragged object is moving over the control.
  Accept - Specifies whether to accept the dragged object.
See Also
  <LINK TJvCustomListBox.CreateDragImage, CreateDragImage>,
  <LINK TJvCustomListBox.DefaultDragDrop, DefaultDragDrop>,
  <LINK TJvCustomListBox.DefaultStartDrag, DefaultStartDrag>,
  TControl.OnDragOver
